LAGOS – The Ezendigbo of Ibadan land and Oyo state, Eze Dr. Alex Anozie and Ndigbo of Ibadan and the state have lauded the Olubadan In Council for resolving the judicial conundrum preventing the new Olubadan of Ibadan from being enthroned. Recalled that an appeal by the Olubadan In Council against their position as Obas were preventing the enthronement of new Olubadan elect, Senator Lekan Balogun who incidentally was an Oba from being crowned as the new Olubadan following the demise of the late Olubadan, Oba Saliu Akanmu Adetunji. In a press release signed by Eze Dr. Anozie, he and Ndigbo in Oyo state commended the Olubadan In Council for resolving the problem by withdrawing their case from the Court of Appeal thus paving the way for the enthronement of the new Olubadan after he was elected by them. Ndigbo Passes Vote Of Confidence In Ohanaeze President-General Obi Cubana: Invitation By NDLEA, Another Ethnic Harassment On… Dr. Anozie praised the Governor for working in concert with them as well as the judiciary to eliminate the legal issue preventing the enthronement of the new Olubadan Senator Lekan Balogun who is the incumbent Otun Olubadan of Ibadanland. The Ezendigbo stated that he and the Ndigbo are very proud of the conduct of the Olubadan In Council by allowing peace to reign for the growth and development of Ibadan land adding that he and the entire Ndigbo in Ibadan and Oyo state are very proud of them individually and collectively. They explained that their conduct was worthy of emulation urging Nigerians to take a cue from the exemplary attitude of the Olubadan In Council.